Lach. reads Exstant usque for Eoestantisque. 406 tibi tum Nauger. first for ubi tzmz. 414 conlectus Lamb. for coniectus: see 111 198. 418 A has properly ut before videare: caelum appears to have come from caeli of 417 or caelo oi 419: see notes 2: Flor. 31 has mirand03 Nico. Camb. etc. miranda. Lach. seems to have misapprehended the matter, as in 213 and 1 1061: he reads Ut prope miraclo for Corpora mirande, caeli for caelo, and transposes the two verses. But I have obeyed him in reading dispicere for despicere, as mS. authority is of little weight on such a point: comp. 421 dis-perimus AB Nicc. for desp. Virgil's mss. both in Aen. 1 224 and georg. 11 187 are nearly all in favour of despicere. Ph. Wagner philologus xv p. 352 quotes on the side of despicere Quintil. inst.
